pageContext.claim: “I had 206 to 223 in the Electoral College -- 306 to 223. And I'm saying to myself, wait a minute, I just won one of the greatest elections of all time in the history of this country -- and even you will admit that -- and now I have somebody writing a report that never got a vote. It's called the Mueller report. So explain that, because my voters don't get it. And I don't get it.”
pageContext.analysis: Hillary Clinton won 232 votes in the Electoral College. Because of several faithless electors, the official count was 304 to 227.
